"670","<TEXT>"
"671","032 Putnam U.S. Government Income Trust"
"672","Regulatory matters and litigation"
"673","In late 2003 and 2004, Putnam Management settled charges brought"
"674","by the SEC and the Massachusetts Securities Division in"
"675","connection with excessive short term trading in Putnam"
"676","funds. In July 2011, the fund recorded a receivable"
"677","of $254,079 related to restitution amounts in connection with a"
"678","distribution plan approved by the SEC. This amount is"
"679","reported in the Increase in capital from settlement"
"680","payments line on the Statement of changes in net"
"681","assets. These allegations and related matters have served as the"
"682","general basis for certain lawsuits, including purported class"
"683","action lawsuits against Putnam Management and, in a limited"
"684","number of cases, some Putnam funds. In May 2011, the fund"
"685","received a payment of $5,150 related to settlement of those"
"686","lawsuits. This amount is reported in the Increase in capital"
"687","from settlement payments line on the Statement of changes"
"688","in net assets.Putnam Management has agreed to bear any costs"
"689","incurred by the Putnam funds as a result of these matters."
